"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-power-ranking-women-s-2024-olympic-soccer-teams-01j1szw15s03\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Janine Beckieput it perfectly, \\\"The Olympics is chaos.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 55, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's exactly what it is.\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 83, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"26 games in just 16 days.\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only two full days in between games.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the World Cup, you get four.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's condensed.\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mentally taxing.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A true challenge like no other.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But in the end, the reward - a Gold Medal - is all worth the struggle.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This time last year we were previewing a field of 32 teams for a major women's football tournament.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Olympics, only 12 qualify.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the cream of the crop.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The elite of the elite from every region around the world.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making it into this prestigious group is difficult enough.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To win the gold is a completely different challenge only four countries have ever managed to do.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the drama begins, it seems like a good idea to lay down some groundwork by power ranking the entire field to get an understanding of where each nation stands at the moment.\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is where these 12 giants from six different confederations rank in relation to each other.\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Group:AWorld Ranking:28  Just weeks before New Zealand's fifth Olympic Games, its head coach since September of 2021, Jitka Klimkov\\u00c3\\u00a1 opted to stand down from her position for the time being.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1016, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.534622302285477e-16, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Insert assistant Michael Mayne.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Mayne\", \"score\": 0.9999651629470557, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Mayne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q42603\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Mayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Mayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The acting head coach leads the Oceania Football Confederation in another major competition, a year after bowing out of the World Cup on home soil in the group stage.\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oceania Football Confederation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's difficult to judge the Football Ferns by virtue of the fact that the Confederation they are in just is not very strong.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They rolled through qualifying, scoring 32 goals in just five games, seven of which were converted by the 25-year-old Grace Jale.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Jale\", \"score\": 0.9999916345118189, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grace Jale\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Jale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Jale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The backline is a clear strength.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That experience in defense showed last summer at the World Cup, allowing one goal in 270 minutes of football.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Six of its seven oldest players are defenders, the most important being Katie Bowen, the Inter Milan center back.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1854, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter_Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0160366859209064e-55, \"text\": \"Inter Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter_Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter_Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan_Center,_Indiana\", \"score\": 0.9999964546886168, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Milan center\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan_Center,_Indiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan_Center,_Indiana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The player to watch on Mayne's crew is Katie Kitching, an ultra hard working midfielder from Sunderland AFC who should be a key piece for the Football Ferns on both sides of the ball.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 2062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayne_Australian_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.9999996429215299, \"rank\": 3.5707476924614e-07, \"text\": \"Mayne\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayne_Australian_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayne_Australian_Football_Club\"}, {\"begin\": 1924, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Kitching\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kitching\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Kitching\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Kitching\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Getting to work in Saint-\\u00c3\\u0089tienne \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ab\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b7\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b3\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00bf#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/dgV9CIt6GE  The question for this team is who can step up on the national stage to be that goal scoring threat it desperately needs?\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not get out of the group stage without goals.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Defensive stability can only take you so far.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Could it be Indiah-Paige Riley of PSV or even the youngster Milly Clegg out of Racing Louisville FC?\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiah-Paige_Riley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Indiah-Paige Riley\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiah-Paige_Riley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiah-Paige_Riley\"}, {\"begin\": 2452, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_Louisville_FC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Racing Louisville FC\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_Louisville_FC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_Louisville_FC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only time will tell.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Group:BWorld Ranking:64  Around this same time in 2019, the women's national team from Zambia was ranked 119th in the world or 15th among Confederation of African Football nations.\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2583, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4851543429561456e-11, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Copper Queens, as they are widely known, have come a long way.\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be their second straight time competing in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In their last outing in Japan, the African outfit finished with just one point, behind both Brazil and the Netherlands in group play.\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2835, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.907273349174553e-29, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2903, \"end\": 2909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.380297451725968e-23, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.96853063345204, \"rank\": 0.03249186495655042, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spearheaded by arguably theworld's most dominant striker, at least in terms of recent form, Barbra Banda from the Orlando Pride, Zambia has what it takes to play spoiler in an extremely tough Group B.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3038, \"end\": 3050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbra Banda\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\"}, {\"begin\": 3060, \"end\": 3073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Pride\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Orlando Pride\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Pride\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Pride\"}, {\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4851543429561456e-11, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3138, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.79185459559734e-12, \"text\": \"Group B\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former Chinese Women's Super League star was spectacular in her previous Olympics, scoring an absurd six goals in three games, tying Sam Kerr and Ellen White for the second most in the tournament.\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3158, \"end\": 3165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"score\": 0.9963948705905061, \"rank\": 0.003618095383460321, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_League_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9988066929941013, \"rank\": 0.0011058409112703713, \"text\": \"Super League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_League_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_League_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 3284, \"end\": 3292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Kerr\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_G._White\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.728303027579191e-50, \"text\": \"Ellen White\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_G._White\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_G._White\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Banda is accompanied by her soon-to-be teammate in Orlando, Grace Chanda, and forward Racheal Kundananji, who cost Bay FC \\u00c2\\u00a3625,000 in transfer fees to obtain in the NWSL offseason.\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\", \"score\": 0.9999597794188605, \"rank\": 3.909484571748012e-05, \"text\": \"Banda\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\"}, {\"begin\": 3399, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\", \"score\": 0.9999999936790118, \"rank\": 6.321417865404815e-09, \"text\": \"Orlando\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\"}, {\"begin\": 3408, \"end\": 3420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Chanda\", \"score\": 0.9999895431629864, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grace Chanda\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Chanda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Chanda\"}, {\"begin\": 3514, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.507043370009347e-50, \"text\": \"NWSL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Women's_Soccer_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Their (Zambia's) ability to transition is better than any team I have seen in world football,\\\" said Emma Hayes on'The Women's Game'with ex-USWNT midfielder Sam Mewis.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3539, \"end\": 3545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4851543429561456e-11, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hayes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 3688, \"end\": 3697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Mewis\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nobody can sleep on Zambia.\", \"from\": 3700, \"to\": 3727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3720, \"end\": 3726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4851543429561456e-11, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This group of players, despite the chaos occurring in its own federation, are a sneaky pick to clinch a spot in the final eight, especially if Banda can repeat her Olympic goal scoring form from 2021.\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 3928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3871, \"end\": 3876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\", \"score\": 0.9999597794188605, \"rank\": 3.909484571748012e-05, \"text\": \"Banda\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hastings_Banda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Group:CWorld Ranking:36  After beating South Africa on aggregate in April, Nigeria earned a place back on the Olympic stage for the first time since Beijing 2008.\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 4092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3969, \"end\": 3981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.870572635645167e-12, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4005, \"end\": 4012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.863734372513978e-23, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Super Falcons are here to make a splash upon their return, potentially using the confidence and momentum from an impressive World Cup showing in 2023 to compete with an even more challenging Olympic field.\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4097, \"end\": 4110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Super Falcons\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few had Randy Waldrum and his Nigeria team doing what it did at the 2023 World Cup.\", \"from\": 4304, \"to\": 4387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4312, \"end\": 4325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Waldrum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Randy Waldrum\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Waldrum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Waldrum\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Super Falcons never actually lost in regulation at this summer's major tournament, falling to England after a valiant effort in penalty kicks.\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4392, \"end\": 4405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Super Falcons\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4486, \"end\": 4493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999989304342, \"rank\": 1.0704264714125064e-09, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The issue for Nigeria is the fact that it is positioned in arguably the toughest group in the entire tournament alongside Japan, Brazil, and reigning world champion Spain.\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4550, \"end\": 4557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.863734372513978e-23, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resour